title: High Female Leadership in Business
description: In 2016, 64.8% of firms in Thailand had female top managers, showcasing a strong representation of women in leadership roles.

title: Comprehensive Birth Registration in Urban Areas
description: As of 2019, Thailand achieved a 100% completeness rate in urban birth registration, ensuring all urban births are officially recorded.

title: Effective Social Insurance Programs
description: In 2021, social insurance programs in Thailand covered 92.99% of the total welfare of beneficiary households, indicating robust social support systems.

title: Minimal Health Expenditure-Induced Poverty
description: By 2021, only 0.01% of Thailand's population was pushed below the $3.65 poverty line due to out-of-pocket health care expenses, reflecting effective health care policies.

title: Low Proportion of Time on Unpaid Domestic Work for Women
description: In 2015, Thai women spent 11.04% of their day on unpaid domestic and care work, one of the lowest globally, suggesting a more balanced domestic workload.

title: Minimal Tariff Lines with Specific Rates on Manufactured Products
description: In 2015, only 0.00045% of Thailand's tariff lines on manufactured products had specific rates, indicating a liberal trade policy.

title: Negative Net Official Flows from UNIDO
description: In 2020, Thailand experienced a net outflow of $2,096.82 from UNIDO, suggesting a need for improved international financial relations.
